
 Lead Management & CRM Dashboard (Wireframe-Based)



 1. Project Overview

Project Name: Lead Management & CRM Dashboard
Client Type: B2B / Sales / CRM Platform
Designer Role: UI/UX Designer (UX Strategy, Wireframing, Interaction Design)
Platform: Responsive Web Application

# Objective

To design a structured, efficient, and user-friendly lead management system that helps sales teams track, manage, and convert leads while gaining clear performance insights through dashboards and filters.



 2. Problem Statement

Sales teams often face challenges such as:

. Scattered lead information
. Manual tracking and follow-ups
. Poor visibility into lead status and salesperson performance
. Time-consuming filtering and searching

Design Goal: Create a centralized CRM interface that simplifies lead tracking, improves sales productivity, and provides actionable insights with minimal effort.



 3. Target Users & Personas

# Primary Users

1. Sales Executives – Managing daily leads & follow-ups
2. Sales Managers – Monitoring team performance
3. Business Owners – Tracking conversion metrics

# User Needs

. Quick access to lead details
. Easy lead creation & updates
. Clear lead status visibility
. Performance analytics
. Efficient filtering & search



 4. User Journey

1. Login to Dashboard
   ↓
2. View Key Metrics & Lead Status Overview
   ↓
3. Browse Lead List
   ↓
4. Filter / Search Specific Leads
   ↓
5. View, Edit, or Add Lead
   ↓
6. Update Status & Daily Notes



 5. Information Architecture

# Primary Navigation

. Dashboard
. Lead List
. Add New Lead
. Lead Details
. Profile

# Filters & Controls

. Lead Status
. Category
. Date / Duration
. Assigned Salesperson
. Search



 6. Design System (Wireframe Level)

# Layout Principles

. Grid-based structure
. Left-to-right information flow
. Table-driven data presentation

# Typography

. Clear sans-serif
. Emphasis on names & statuses

# UI Principles

. Speed & efficiency
. Data-first design
. Minimal distractions
. Consistency across screens



 7. Screen-wise UX Breakdown

# 7.1 Dashboard Screen

Purpose: High-level sales performance overview

Key Elements:

. Total leads
. Contacted leads
. Converted leads
. Uninterested leads
. Lead status distribution

UX Decisions:

. Metrics placed at the top for instant visibility
. Status breakdown to identify bottlenecks



# 7.2 Lead Listing Screen

Purpose: Central lead management view

Key Elements:

. Lead table (Name, Contact, Email, Status, Date, Assigned Salesperson)
. Filters & search bar
. Pagination

UX Strategy:

. Table layout for quick scanning
. Filters placed above the list
. Status tags for visual clarity



# 7.3 Lead Details View

Purpose: Deep dive into individual lead

Content:

. Personal details
. Lead status
. Assigned salesperson
. Daily updates / notes

UX Rationale:

. Grouped information blocks
. Editable fields with clear CTAs
. Notes section for ongoing communication tracking



# 7.4 Add / Edit Lead Screen

Purpose: Fast lead creation & modification

Fields:

. Full name
. Email
. Contact number
. Lead status
. Category
. Assigned salesperson
. Date

UX Decisions:

. Simple form layout
. Logical field order
. Save & edit actions clearly separated



 8. Interaction Design

. Status change via dropdowns
. Inline edit options
. Clear VIEW / EDIT buttons
. Visual confirmation on save



 9. Accessibility & Usability Considerations

. Clear labels for form fields
. Consistent status indicators
. Keyboard-friendly navigation
. Readable spacing for dense data



 10. Scalability Considerations

. Modular lead cards
. Expandable filters
. Support for large lead volumes
. Future CRM integrations



 11. Tools Used

. Wireframing: Figma
. UX Planning: User flow & IA diagrams



 12. Future Enhancements

. Automation for follow-ups
. Lead scoring system
. Sales performance analytics
. Role-based access control
. CRM & email integration



 13. Conclusion

This wireframe-driven UI/UX design focuses on operational efficiency, clarity, and scalability. It empowers sales teams with structured workflows, real-time visibility, and simplified lead management—laying a strong foundation for a full-featured CRM product.



Designed by: Sanskrati Agrawal
Role: UI/UX Designer
